parameters: <She hasn't seen me yet, maybe I can->
Uhh... Now I know how this looks...
W-Wait! Wait a minute!! IT’S NOT-
Unbelievable!!! You think you can save my life,
and just waltz in here like it’s your own
I THOUGHT THE STALL WAS EMPTY!!!
You're the one that told me to use this shower!!
Now I’ve got you, you little-
If you would just LISTEN to me,
you’d know that I wasn’t trying to spy on you!
Look, I don’t blame you for being on edge, and I don't
blame you for not trusting me, but...
Can we please talk about it?
Yes! I heard you the first time, \N[001]!
You almost drowned, and we could have been eaten by a shark.
Today was crazy and I wanted to check on you...
I didn’t want to just leave you hanging...
*Ahem*... I... Yes, thank you, \N[001]. That was considerate
of you to ask. I’m... Sorry that I presumed the worst
after... Especially after what you just did for me.
It's ok... I should be thanking you for saving my ass, too.
Oh, and sorry for flashing you there.
<How can he act so nonchalant about... THAT!>
I- well, I mean... At least we're even, I suppose...
<EVEN?? What the hell does that mean?
So... Did you get anything for your book?
I’m certain there’s plenty to work with, yes...
Great. Um... Until next time I guess..?
You... You still want to continue with this? Even after...
Of course I do. I mean, if you’re still up for it.
Maybe for our next date we could do something slightly-
Safer, I agree. Precisely the same thought I had.
Unless you want to just call the whole
thing off now. If you forfeit the bet,
does that mean I get a passing grade?
Me? Backing out? I don’t think so.
For our next “date”... Why don’t we see a movie together?
It’s simple, and should give me a baseline on how my
characters would interact in more... Mundane conditions.
I could go for a movie, sure.
Just say when, and I’ll be there.
Perfect, I think I remember seeing that the Double Dome
Theater has matinees Wednesday evenings, we can meet there
after class if that works for you.
A movie is probably a much more relaxing way to spend time
together...  Today was a lot - try to get some rest, and
forget about the monster you saw today...
I- Umm... Goodbye, \n[1]... I'll see you in class...
I'm gonna grab a shower before I head home...
<You can’t make this shit up. I killed an evil monster-shark!
But more importantly, I’m glad Brenda is safe...>
<And that she’s starting to feel a bit more “inspired”... >
<I need... I need to get to my computer.
I have to get these thoughts out while they're fresh!>
